background_story: Dearestone was a profound thinker who spent his life pondering the mysteries of the universe. He became particularly fascinated with the concept of circularity, believing that all things in life are interconnected and cyclical. Dearestone proposed that events, ideas, and even time itself are part of an eternal loop, where endings mark new beginnings. His theory, known as the 'Dearestone Cycle,' suggested that every action, thought, and phenomenon is linked in a grand, cosmic dance. Through his writings and teachings, Dearestone inspired a new generation of thinkers to explore the intricacies of circularity, encouraging them to seek harmony and balance within the ever-turning wheel of existence.
